24/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Executives from several major US and British defence contractors, including Lockheed Martin, General Dynamics and BAE, reaffirmed their commitment Monday (23 June) to helping Bulgaria revamp and modernise its armed forces. The executives were in Sofia for an international conference on potential business opportunities following Bulgaria's accession to NATO. In his speech to participants, President Georgi Parvanov described the defence industry as one of the country's key assets. Other participants included representatives from Lucent Technologies, IBM Global Services and Harris Corporation. (Dnevnik, Trud, 24 Chassa - 24/06/03; AFP, BNT - 23/06/03)
